In mathematics, the '''Chebyshev integral''', named after [[Pafnuty Chebyshev]], is
: <math>\int x^p (1-x)^q \, dx = B (x; 1+p, 1+q),</math>
where <math> B (x; a, b) </math> is an [[incomplete beta function]].
